The paper discusses the use of AI algorithms to assist humans in decision-making tasks, which falls under the category of AI. The study also involves observing human-agent teams and their performance, which relates to human-computer interaction (HC). The use of a multi-armed bandit as a controlled setting suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of machine learning (LG) or cybernetics (CY). Finally, the paper discusses the need to understand how the agent's suggestions influence human decision-making, which relates to social and information sciences (SI).
